nologically advanced hospital in the world in 4 by top master’s in healthcare administration partnered with siemens to reduce energy costs while embracing new technology that integrates building automation and patient room temperature control drives quality care environments and improves patient satisfaction download the case study more close perfect place to heal safely the yakima regional medical  cardiac center’s national rankings awards certifications and accreditations demonstrate the entire team’s desire to deliver excellent care    to help keep prepared for the joint commission nfpa or local surveyor visits siemens proposed a fire  life safety service program and a healthcare accreditation program that allows the center to confidently greet any surveyor – keeping the center’s operations and more importantly patient care uninterrupted download the case study more close digitalization how can you create the perfect place buildings are alive with information  billions of intelligent devices and machines generate massive amounts of data every day every hour every second  and with the right digital tools you can now learn from them and interact with them like never before  only when you understand the information available from your buildings can you best determine how to turn them into perfect places as a leader in the digital transformation knowing how to analyze building data enables us to continuously optimize our customers’ building performance – creating real value in their operations and supporting them in creating perfect places perfect place for big data today everything is based on data – and data centers must deliver speed and scalability to successfully serve as the backbone of entire industries learn how the global data center player digital realty together with siemens grew their colocation site network by scaling to meet customer needs at unrivaled speeds learn more about digital realty more close perfect place for smart operations transparency is the key to greater energy and operational efficiency navigator siemens’ powerful analytics platform acquires and analyzes performance data for every building in your portfolio the result comprehensive insights in an easytouse cloudbased platform that tells you – and our service experts – exactly what your building needs to deliver peak performance   watch the demo more close perfect place for business can your building be more than four walls and a roof what if it created the perfect place for you your business and your customers with an intelligent infrastructure your building becomes one continuous source of actionable data it contributes to improvements enabling smarter operations and creating the perfect environment for you to focus on the goals that drive your business forward learn how to make smart buildings more profitable more close building performance  sustainability something drives us to make buildings better with people spending about  percent of their lives indoors there is no place where we spend more time in our life so buildings are far more than just four walls they are the places where we learn the most important lessons in life where we encounter the personalities that inspire us where the best of our ideas are born   perfect place to live the city of monterey park california has begun working toward its green agenda by leveraging both new energy efficient technologies as well as an innovative financing arrangement that guarantees energy savings to the city with led lighting upgrades a new building automation system siemens desigo cc™ energyefficient hvac technologies and a new bluetoothenabled automatic water meter reading system siemens is helping the city of monterey park have a positive impact on both the community and the environment says mayor hans liang “it’s not easy for a municipality to commit to spending large amounts of money even when we’re investing in a more sustainable future but with siemens costneutral program we’re guaranteed those energy savings”   watch the video download the case study more close siemens  challenges concerning building’s energy consumption many building owners are not aware of the amount of energy theirbuildings consume and most buildings in the world consume much more energy than necessary worldwide energy consumption 4buildings mobility industry leverage the value of transparency the first step to unleashing a building’s full potential is toachieve transparency of the current situation and makinguse of all the data available nowadays analyze energy supply and demandfrom single building to a global network of buildings reduction in energy costs increase buildinginfrastructure performance navigator powered by synalytics use the potentials get most out of your buildings and infrastructure comprehensive insightful and intuitive advantage™ navigator combines analytics with siemens expertise in energy supply demand management and performanceconsolidating data across systems to deliver insights as broad or as focused as your needs demand connectcollect analyze and optimize   users   data points siemens improving building’sperformance 4buildings optimized million tons less co emitted into the atmosphere each year  billioneuros energy cost savings buildings serviced continuous data analysis five phases lead towards energyefficient sustainable and highperformance buildings measurement  reporting evaluation  assessment program implementation ongoing services  optimization strategy  planning data transparency used to meet the challenges and gain competitiveness cost reduction performance increase sustainability asset value increase one answer against climate change buildings account for 4 percent of energy consumption worldwide and produce a third of greenhouse gas emissions as public opinion calls for more environmental transparency and accountability from public and commercial organizations improving your buildings’ efficiency is a necessary move but it is also a smart one wit